Statement of changes (Apache License 2.0, Section 4(b))
================================================================================

FreeSense modifies the upstream pfSense CE source as follows:

  * Rebranding of the product name, paths, namespaces, strings, and assets
    from "pfSense" to "FreeSense".
  * Removal of vendor-private (Netgate) build dependencies and components that
    are not part of the open-source distribution, to allow building entirely
    from public sources.
  * Build-system changes to produce a bootable ISO without the original
    vendor's private build infrastructure.

"pfSense" is a registered trademark of Electric Sheep Fencing, LLC, licensed to
Netgate. The pfSense name and marks are used here only to accurately identify the
upstream project from which FreeSense is derived, and are not used as FreeSense's
own branding.

